      "content": "thanks for that. i've already looked through some old league of nations papers but things get really blurry around the late 40s. it's like someone went to great lengths to redact everything. i have this scanned document from my grandfather—he was part of the provisional council—that mentions a specific treaty called the \"Samarkand Accord\" which supposedly guaranteed our borders under international supervision. if that document is real and the treaty exists, what would be the formal legal process for a legitimate heir to petition for the recognition of a dissolved state's sovereignty today?",
